| `tail` | Display last lines of file | `tail -f /var/log/syslog`<br>`tail -n 50 error.log` | `ğŸ“„ [Last 10 lines] â† tail â† [Full File]` |
| `find` | Search for files in directory hierarchy | `find /home -name "*.txt"`<br>`find . -type f -mtime -7` | `ğŸ” Search Tree: / â†’ dir1 â†’ dir2 â†’ [MATCH!]` |
| `locate` | Find files by name (uses database) | `locate nginx.conf`<br>`updatedb` (update database) | `[Database] â†’ locate keyword â†’ [Fast Results]` |
| `which` | Show full path of commands | `which python`<br>`which ls` | `Command â†’ which â†’ [/usr/bin/command]` |
| `ln` | Create links between files | `ln -s /path/to/file link`<br>`ln file hardlink` | `ğŸ“„ Original âŸ· ğŸ”— Symlink â†’ Points to Original` |
| `tree` | Display directory structure | `tree -L 2`<br>`tree -a` | `ğŸ“ root`<br>`â”œâ”€â”€ ğŸ“ dir1`<br>`â””â”€â”€ ğŸ“„ file` |

