## 6. Disk, Storage & File Systems

Manage disks, partitions, and storage devices.

| Command | Description | Example Usage | Visual/Diagram Explanation |
|---------|-------------|---------------|----------------------------|
| `df` | Report file system disk space | `df -h`<br>`df -i` (inodes) | `ğŸ’¾ /dev/sda1 [â–ˆâ–ˆâ–ˆâ–ˆâ–‘] 75% Used (20GB/100GB)` |
| `du` | Estimate file space usage | `du -sh /var/log`<br>`du -h --max-depth=1` | `ğŸ“ Directory â†’ [Size: 2.5GB]` |
| `fdisk` | Partition table manipulator | `fdisk -l`<br>`fdisk /dev/sdb` | `ğŸ’¿ Disk â†’ [Part1: 50GB] [Part2: 100GB]` |
| `parted` | Partition editor | `parted /dev/sda print` | `[MBR/GPT] â†’ Partitions â†’ [Type, Size, FS]` |
| `mkfs` | Build Linux file system | `mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1`<br>`mkfs.xfs /dev/sdc1` | `[Raw Partition] â†’ mkfs â†’ [Formatted: ext4]` |
| `mount` | Mount file system | `mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt`<br>`mount -t nfs server:/share /mnt` | `ğŸ’¿ Device â†’ mount â†’ ğŸ“ /mnt [Accessible]` |
| `umount` | Unmount file system | `umount /mnt`<br>`umount -l /mnt` (lazy) | `ğŸ“ /mnt [Mounted] â†’ umount â†’ [Unmounted]` |
| `lsblk` | List block devices | `lsblk`<br>`lsblk -f` (filesystems) | `sda [Disk] â”œâ”€sda1 [Part] â””â”€sda2 [Part]` |
| `blkid` | Locate/print block device attributes | `blkid`<br>`blkid /dev/sda1` | `/dev/sda1: UUID="..." TYPE="ext4"` |
| `dd` | Convert and copy files | `dd if=/dev/sda of=/backup.img bs=4M`<br>`dd if=/dev/zero of=file bs=1M count=100` | `Input â†’ [Raw Copy] â†’ Output (Dangerous! âš ï¸)` |
| `fsck` | File system consistency check | `fsck /dev/sda1`<br>`fsck -y /dev/sdb1` | `ğŸ’¿ FS â†’ [Check & Repair] â†’ [Fixed Errors]` |
| `tune2fs` | Adjust ext2/ext3/ext4 parameters | `tune2fs -l /dev/sda1` | `[FS Parameters] â†’ Reserved Blocks, Labels` |
| `resize2fs` | Resize ext2/ext3/ext4 file systems | `resize2fs /dev/sda1` | `[FS: 50GB] â†’ resize â†’ [FS: 100GB]` |
| `mkswap` | Set up Linux swap area | `mkswap /dev/sdb2` | `[Partition] â†’ mkswap â†’ [Swap Space]` |
| `swapon` | Enable swap space | `swapon /dev/sdb2`<br>`swapon -a` | `ğŸ’¾ Swap â†’ [Inactive] â†’ swapon â†’ [Active]` |
| `swapoff` | Disable swap space | `swapoff /dev/sdb2` | `ğŸ’¾ Swap â†’ [Active] â†’ swapoff â†’ [Inactive]` |
| `ncdu` | NCurses disk usage analyzer | `ncdu /home` | `Interactive: [ğŸ“] Navigate & Analyze Usage` |

### ğŸ’¾ File System Hierarchy

```
/ (root)
â”œâ”€â”€ /bin       â†’ Essential binaries (ls, cat, cp)
â”œâ”€â”€ /boot      â†’ Boot loader files (kernel)
â”œâ”€â”€ /dev       â†’ Device files (sda, tty)
â”œâ”€â”€ /etc       â†’ Configuration files
â”œâ”€â”€ /home      â†’ User home directories
â”œâ”€â”€ /lib       â†’ Shared libraries
â”œâ”€â”€ /mnt       â†’ Temporary mount points
â”œâ”€â”€ /opt       â†’ Optional software
â”œâ”€â”€ /proc      â†’ Process information (virtual)
â”œâ”€â”€ /root      â†’ Root user home
â”œâ”€â”€ /sbin      â†’ System binaries (fsck, reboot)
â”œâ”€â”€ /tmp       â†’ Temporary files
â”œâ”€â”€ /usr       â†’ User programs and data
â””â”€â”€ /var       â†’ Variable data (logs, cache)
```

### ğŸ“¦ Partition Types

```
Primary Partition:  Max 4 per disk (MBR)
Extended Partition: Container for logical partitions
Logical Partition:  Inside extended partition

GPT (GUID Partition Table):
- Supports 128+ partitions
- Disks > 2TB
- Modern standard
```

### ğŸ¯ Cheat Sheet: Storage

```bash
# Disk space analysis
df -h | grep -v tmpfs              # Real filesystems only
du -sh /* | sort -h                # Top-level directories by size
ncdu /var                          # Interactive disk usage

# Mounting operations
mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt               # Mount partition
mount -o remount,rw /              # Remount as read-write
cat /etc/fstab                     # Auto-mount configuration

# Create swap file
dd if=/dev/zero of=/swapfile bs=1G count=4
mkswap /swapfile
swapon /swapfile

# Check filesystem
umount /dev/sda1                   # Must unmount first
fsck -y /dev/sda1                  # Auto-fix errors
```

### âš ï¸ Critical Warnings
- **NEVER** run `dd` without triple-checking parameters
- **ALWAYS** unmount before running `fsck`
- Backup data before `fdisk` operations
- `mkfs` **destroys all data** on partition

---

## 7. Package Management

Install, update, and manage software packages across different Linux distributions.

| Command | Description | Example Usage | Visual/Diagram Explanation |
|---------|-------------|---------------|----------------------------|
| **Debian/Ubuntu (APT)** | | | |
| `apt update` | Update package index | `apt update` | `[Local Index] â† sync â† [Remote Repos]` |
| `apt upgrade` | Upgrade installed packages | `apt upgrade`<br>`apt full-upgrade` | `ğŸ“¦ v1.0 â†’ upgrade â†’ ğŸ“¦ v2.0` |
| `apt install` | Install packages | `apt install nginx`<br>`apt install -y docker.io` | `[Repository] â†’ download â†’ [Installed] âœ“` |
| `apt remove` | Remove packages | `apt remove apache2`<br>`apt purge nginx` | `ğŸ“¦ Package â†’ remove â†’ [Uninstalled]` |
| `apt search` | Search packages | `apt search python` | `[Query: python] â†’ [Results: python3, pip...]` |
| `apt show` | Show package details | `apt show nginx` | `Package: nginx | Version: 1.18 | Deps: ...` |
| `apt autoremove` | Remove unused dependencies | `apt autoremove` | `[Orphaned Packages] â†’ [Cleaned]` |
| **RedHat/CentOS (YUM/DNF)** | | | |
| `yum update` | Update all packages | `yum update` | `[System Packages] â†’ update â†’ [Latest]` |
| `yum install` | Install package | `yum install httpd` | `[Repo] â†’ install â†’ [httpd installed]` |
| `yum remove` | Remove package | `yum remove nginx` | `ğŸ“¦ nginx â†’ [Removed]` |
| `yum search` | Search for package | `yum search python` | `[Query] â†’ [Matching Packages]` |
| `dnf` | Next-gen YUM (Fedora/RHEL 8+) | `dnf install vim` | `[Faster YUM] with better dependency solving` |
| **Arch Linux (Pacman)** | | | |
| `pacman -Syu` | Sync and update system | `pacman -Syu` | `[Repos] â†’ sync â†’ [Update All]` |
| `pacman -S` | Install package | `pacman -S firefox` | `[AUR/Repo] â†’ install â†’ [firefox]` |
| `pacman -R` | Remove package | `pacman -R package` | `ğŸ“¦ â†’ [Removed]` |
| `pacman -Ss` | Search packages | `pacman -Ss python` | `[Query] â†’ [Results from repos]` |
| **Universal Tools** | | | |
| `dpkg` | Debian package manager | `dpkg -i package.deb`<br>`dpkg -l` (list) | `ğŸ“¦ .deb â†’ dpkg â†’ [Installed]` |
| `rpm` | RedHat package manager | `rpm -ivh package.rpm`<br>`rpm -qa` (list) | `ğŸ“¦ .rpm â†’ rpm â†’ [Installed]` |
| `snap` | Universal package manager | `snap install vscode`<br>`snap refresh` | `[Snap Store] â†’ [Sandboxed App]` |
| `flatpak` | Universal app distribution | `flatpak install firefox` | `[Flathub] â†’ [Containerized App]` |
| `pip` | Python package installer | `pip install requests`<br>`pip3 install flask` | `[PyPI] â†’ download â†’ [Python Package]` |
| `npm` | Node.js package manager | `npm install express`<br>`npm update` | `[npmjs.com] â†’ [node_modules]` |

### ğŸ“¦ Package Management Flow

```
APT (Debian/Ubuntu):
[/etc/apt/sources.list] â†’ apt update â†’ [Local Cache]
                                            â†“
User: apt install pkg â†’ [Check Cache] â†’ Download â†’ Install â†’ Configure

YUM/DNF (RedHat/CentOS):
[/etc/yum.repos.d/] â†’ yum update â†’ [Metadata Cache]
                                        â†“
User: yum install pkg â†’ Resolve Deps â†’ Download â†’ Install
```

